The Adamawa state chapter of the Nigerian Union of Teachers (NUT), has donated Toyota picnic car, to facilitate smooth administration of student’s activities in the state. Comrade Haddafi Hussaini, President, National Union of Adamawa State Students (NUADSS), Monday lauded Nathan Rodney the state chairman for the gesture. Hussaini urge government to complete dilapidated secretariat of the union, named after Gov Ahmadu Fintiri for his role in the payment of scholarship. He assured that, the union cannot be used as venture for distribution of money. “The union would use the mobility for tour to identify our colleague plight with a view to addressing them.” He lauded the payment of scholarship to over 26,000 students by the state government. The student union leader further revealed that, the union had address all issues with faction in the union. “We have risen above our differences and successfully united into strong formidable union.” 